speech.p:
asked the Secretary of State for Scotland (1) what requirements, under town and country planning law, he has imposed to protect the beauties of Clackmannanshire from spoliation by the growth of pit bings;

(2) whether he is aware that the scenery in Clackmannanshire will be spoilt by unsightly bings of refuse which may result


from the proposed large coal development; and whether he will ensure that suitable trees are planted to grow with the bings and preserve the amenities.
